<br>
k, strap in, here we go...<br>
&lt;hr&gt;<br>
&lt;i&gt; Note - I did this on my win2k machine, so im not promising it will work on other operating systems. Im also not promising that it'll work on win2k, but It works on mine *shrug* and, if you're afraid of screwing up your registry beyond repair, make sure you save the previous setting before you go wacking away at bin codes...&lt;/i&gt;<br>
<br>
Go under the start menu, select run, type &quot;regedit&quot; hit enter.<br>
<br>
This is your registry - for those of you unfamiliar with it, this is where you erm...own your friend's computers from and they can never figure out how to fix it.<br>
<br>
K, now, go under this folder, (or key, as we like to call it)<br>
<br>
HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\SYSTEM\CurrentControlSet\Control\Keyboard Layout<br>
<br>
In that folder you will see an entry, or &quot;value&quot; called &quot;Scancode Map&quot; Data type should be &quot;REG_BINARY&quot;<br>
<br>
If its not there you'll need to make one. Right click, you should get a &quot;new&quot; tab, go over, select &quot;binary value&quot; and click it.<br>
<br>
Name it &quot;Scancode Map&quot;<br>
<br>
Double click &quot;Scancode Map&quot; whether you just created it, or it was already there.<br>
<br>
You'll get a box that says &quot;Value data:&quot;<br>
<br>
It should have &quot;0000&quot; and then an area to type. <br>
<br>
Type in this exactly...<br>
<br>
00 00 00 00 00 00 00 00 03 00 00 00 00 00 5B E0 00 00 5C E0 00 00 00 00<br>
<br>
That should do it - might want to save the original value list (if it was there, otherwise you can just delete this to go back to the original setup) incase it facks up your machine, but that screws j00r windows button good =P<br>
<br>
You most likely will have to restart in order for it to work...and remember, I have win2k, so I dunno if it'll work on everyone's registry.<br>
<br>
Edit - Remember, screwing with your registry can be seriously hazardous to your computer's health. If you have no clue what youre doing, and deviate from the above, it may result in cancer, heart disease, etc. If for some reason you screw your computer to hell, backup your files, take 1 dose of format, and another dose of Reinstalling your Operating System, and call me in the morning.<br>
<br>
-Drakz<br>
